- Baker initially made 43 cakes.
- He also made 114 pastries.
- He sold 78 cakes.
- And he sold 154 pastries.

\( 154 \text{ (pastries sold)} - 78 \text{ (cakes sold)} = 76 \).

Therefore, Baker sold 76 more pastries than cakes.

The answer is: 76.
